Preconditions:
The input string `s` must not be null.
The input array `indices` must not be null.
The input arrays `sources` and `targets` must not be null.
The lengths of the input arrays `indices`, `sources`, and `targets` must be the same.

Postconditions:
The resulting string after performing all replacement operations on `s` will be returned.
The resulting string will have the same length as the original string `s`.
The resulting string will have the replacements applied based on the indices, sources, and targets provided.
If there are no replacements to be made, the resulting string will be the same as the original string `s`.